  "prompt": "Is it a good idea to let someone know how you feel?",
  "response": "That depends on the specific situation, but generally:\n\nPros of sharing your feelings:\n- Provides clarity and honesty\n- Can lead to deeper understanding\n- Might resolve misunderstandings\n- Potential for positive connection\n- Reduces emotional burden of keeping feelings hidden\n\nCons or risks:\n- Potential rejection\n- Possible awkwardness\n- Could change existing relationship dynamics\n- Might make the other person uncomfortable\n\nFactors to consider:\n- Nature of your relationship\n- Timing\n- Emotional readiness\n- Potential consequences\n- Your own emotional well-being\n\nThe best approach is usually to:\n- Be honest but respectful\n- Choose an appropriate moment\n- Be prepared for any outcome\n- Prioritize your emotional health\n\nEach situation is unique, so there's no universal \"right\" answer.",
